									README
##-----------------------------------------------------------------------------##
# GEOCONVERTOR JAVA API version BETA - Converts coordinate latitude/longitude.
# https://github.com/razec/geoconvertor


News: (For news, check CHANGELOG file) and http://code.google.com/p/geoconvertor/

What is this?

The geoconvertor it's API JAVA created to convert coordinates using complex geodesic equation. 

Supporting three conversions:

	Decimal Coordinate to UTM
		Easily convert between latitude/longitude, Universal Transverse Mercator (UTM) using DATUM: SAD69 and WGS-84.
	DMS (Degrees, Minutes, Seconds) to Decimal Degree
	
	Decimal Degree to DMS (Degrees, Minutes, Seconds)

Pre-requisites:

Java:
- Java Runtime Environment Version 5.0

How to install?

1) Adding geoconvertor-v0.x.jar api to the project.

2) Import
import org.geoconvertor.datum.Datum;
import org.geoconvertor.utm.GEOConvertor;

Construct an object:

GEOConvertor gcv = new GEOConvertor(); 

Call the methods:

geoToUTM(decimal_latitude, decimal_longitude, datum, central_meridian);
decToDMS(decimal_coordinate);
dmsToDec(dms_coordinate); 

More Information: https://github.com/razec/geoconvertor/wiki


